              body: "PAS is the workhorse of direct response. **Problem**: name the pain precisely, in VOC language — 'you post consistently and your reach keeps shrinking.' **Agitate**: press on it; make the cost vivid and the future trajectory clear — 'every month this continues, the algorithm learns your content is skippable, and the hole gets deeper. Meanwhile smaller accounts in your niche are signing brand deals.' **Solution**: present the way out and the mechanism that makes it credible.\n\nAgitation is where amateurs flinch and professionals earn their fee. It is not cruelty — it is honesty about consequences the reader is already privately afraid of. Done right, the reader feels understood, not attacked; the test is whether they would say 'finally, someone gets it.'\n\nPAS wins when the audience already feels the problem. It converts existing pain into action. If they do not yet know they have the problem, PAS reads as noise — you need a different tool."
