              h: "Discovery Before Pitch",
              body: "The amateur DM seller pitches at 'hello.' The professional runs discovery — and discovery is 80% of the close.\n\nA four-beat question arc, adapted from consultative-selling tradition (SPIN, by any name):\n\n1. **Situation**: 'What are you selling / what does your account do right now?' — establishes context, signals interest.\n2. **Problem**: 'What's the biggest thing slowing that down?' — they name the pain in their own words. Their words, note, become your close.\n3. **Implication**: 'What happens if that's still true in six months?' — the cost of inaction, surfaced by *them*, which lands ten times harder than you asserting it.\n4. **Payoff**: 'If that were fixed, what would that be worth?' — they articulate the value of the solution before hearing the price.\n\nBy beat four, the prospect has sold themselves or disqualified themselves — both outcomes are wins. Only now, permission gate: 'Want me to share how I'd approach it?' A yes converts the conversation from cold outreach to requested help. That distinction is everything."
