              body: "A proven shape (adapt lengths to your offer's weight):\n\n1. **Deliver + set the stage** — the asset, instantly, plus one sentence of what is coming: 'this week I'll show you the three shifts behind [outcome].'\n2. **Origin story** — why you do this; the struggle-turn-lesson arc. Trust is transferred through narrative, not credentials.\n3. **The belief shift** — the one idea that separates your method from what they have already tried ('you don't have a content problem, you have an offer problem'). This email does the heaviest selling without selling anything.\n4. **Proof parade** — case studies in BAB shape, chosen to hit 'won't work for me' edge cases.\n5. **The offer** — plainly presented: promise, mechanism, stack, price, one CTA. No apology.\n6. **Objections + FAQ** — the five-roots grid, answered in Q&A format.\n7. **Honest close** — a real reason to act now (founding price, expiring bonus) or a graceful handoff to your regular cadence.\n\nOne idea and one CTA per email. Every email valuable even to never-buyers — that keeps opens alive through the pitch."
