              h: "The Metric Stack",
              body: "Read ad accounts top-down, each metric isolating one layer of the machine:\n\n- **CPM** (cost per 1,000 impressions) — the price of attention in your market. Mostly determined by audience and season; largely outside your control.\n- **Hook rate** — 3-second views ÷ impressions. Your first-frame quality. For cold traffic, seasoned buyers want this in the ~25-40% zone; below that, nothing downstream matters.\n- **Hold rate** — 15s+ views ÷ 3s views. Your body-content quality: did the hook's promise get developed?\n- **CTR** (click-through rate) — desire plus a functioning CTA. Sub-1% on cold traffic usually flags a creative-offer mismatch.\n- **CPC → CPA** (cost per click → cost per acquisition) — the money funnel: what a visitor costs, what a buyer costs.\n- **ROAS** (return on ad spend) — revenue ÷ spend, the scoreboard, judged against your margin: a 3x ROAS on a 70%-margin digital product prints money; the same 3x on 20% margins loses it.\n\nThe power move: never react to ROAS alone — walk the stack top-down and fix the *first* broken layer."
